				Cassie, tanks probably ask for augment cause they don't know any better, that's what they are used to asking for.  It's just like the n00bies asking a lvl 40 chanter for breeze, they are just used to asking for a certain spell....just a tad of ignorance.<BR>
<BR>
My beef with Augment is: I join the group...I get everyone claritied up, I get those tanks aug'd..then sit down to med and see the message &quot;So-and-So feels much faster&quot;  and you know why...the Shaman just cast quickness on them.  This is the most aggrivating thing I am dealing with right now, so aggrivating that I have gone back to alcrity every 6 minutes when there's a damn Shaman in the group, and I am casting tepid deeds over thier &quot;slow spell&quot; too cause I am pissed off!<BR>
My reason's for this...I have figured out that aug. has taken a dive in haste to make up for the other buffs it gives, and the fact that it is more mana efficient and a longer lasting buff.  But why the hell should the lvl 16 spell be able to cover it, couldn't VERANT make it just good enough that F****n' quickness can't cover it, OMG it's almost insulting in a way...here I am lvl 35 have worked hard to achieve my status to &quot;speed the tanks&quot;  and a Shaman, the same lvl as I, with a spell that I have had, and discarded, over 16 lvls ago, can cast over my new shiney toy &quot;AUGMENT&quot;<BR>
<BR>
Well I think it's just BS and if quickness is not a better buff, which it SHOULDN'T BE!  should not cover aug.<BR>
<BR>
Til then, I'll be casting alcrity when in a group with a Shaman, and TEPID DEEDS too, ours covers it so it MUST BE BETTER RIGHT!!!!!<BR>
<BR>
<BR>
My Beef, feel free to Flame
